Closing Summary
---------------

StellarKit API is a developer-focused API wrapper for the Stellar Horizon blockchain. It abstracts common Horizon workflows into easy-to-consume REST endpoints while adding validation, response normalization, security middleware, and TypeScript-friendly declarations.

The project is built for rapid development and production readiness. It is an ideal starting point for teams building wallets, explorers, dashboards, token issuers, or financial applications on Stellar.

By providing a clear route structure, robust middleware, and a modular codebase, StellarKit API helps developers move faster while retaining control over Stellar-specific behavior.

Whether you are testing on Stellar testnet or deploying to mainnet, this repository supports both networks and provides the tools needed to build reliable Stellar integrations.

If you want to contribute, add new functionality, or customize the behavior, the codebase is structured to make it easy to extend while maintaining a consistent API contract.
